mha4mysql-manager - Master High Availability Manager and tools for MySQL (MHA) for automating master failover and fast master switch. This package contains manager scripts.
See https://github.com/yoshinorim/mha4mysql-manager/wiki for details.

MariaDB GTID replication
========================

The manager supports native MariaDB GTID replication in addition to MySQL
GTID on MariaDB 10.0 and newer, including MariaDB 11.x and 12.x. During an
online switch, MariaDB 10.10 and newer use MASTER_DEMOTE_TO_SLAVE=1; older
MariaDB versions fall back to MASTER_USE_GTID=current_pos for the former
primary. Regular replicas always use the safer MASTER_USE_GTID=slave_pos. The
SQL compatibility checks are verified against MariaDB 10.11.18 and 12.1.2.

Required settings on every possible primary include:

  [mariadb]
  server_id=101                 # unique on every server
  log_bin=mariadb-bin
  log_slave_updates=ON
  gtid_strict_mode=ON           # strongly recommended

Configure replicas with native MariaDB GTID positioning:

  CHANGE MASTER TO
    MASTER_HOST='db-primary',
    MASTER_USER='repl',
    MASTER_PASSWORD='secret',
    MASTER_USE_GTID=slave_pos;

Set use_gtid_auto_pos=1 in the MHA application configuration (this remains the
option name for compatibility with existing MySQL configurations). The option
is enabled by default.

MariaDB requirements and limitations:

* Keep a single GTID domain for a normal single-primary topology and use a
  unique server_id on every node.
* log_slave_updates must be enabled on promotion candidates. The manager
  excludes unsafe candidates when GTID failover is active.
* Mixed MySQL/MariaDB topologies do not use GTID auto-position because the two
  GTID formats are incompatible. They fall back to the existing file/position
  recovery path.
* MariaDB multi-source replication is outside MHA's single-source topology
  model.

MariaDB references:

* https://mariadb.com/docs/server/ha-and-performance/standard-replication/gtid
* https://mariadb.com/docs/server/reference/sql-statements/administrative-sql-statements/replication-statements/change-master-to
* https://mariadb.com/docs/server/reference/sql-functions/secondary-functions/miscellaneous-functions/master_gtid_wait
